Verify and submit to Generic Batch Trade
This loop launches Generic Batch Trade in Chrome.  It will try three times to reload the site if unsuccessful.  The delay between retries
is set in the configuration file with vGBTretryDelaySeconds.
Sometimes Chrome displays a popup on a forced shutdown.  This checks for and closes it if found.
If the verify button is present, we can confirm that the site was launched successfully and set the flag to exit the loop.
If the verify button is not found, Chrome is killed and the bot waits a configurable number of seconds to retry

Capture the output message from verification and compare to the value stored in the config file.  Send an exception on failure.
If verification is a success, continue with the submission process.
If a warning is found in GBT's status message, send a notification to the business.  This is not an exception, so the file will be submitted.
